  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of the legal framework surrounding money laundering:\n\n1. International Level\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. United States\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Money Laundering Control Act\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Implemented by agencies like FinCEN\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Customer due diligence\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting large cash transactions\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Corporate and individual liability\n\n5. Compliance Obligations\n- Financial institutions must implement anti-money laundering (AML) programs\n- Regular risk assessments\n- Staff training\n- Internal controls and reporting mechanisms\n\n6. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Extradition agreements\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n\n7. Emerging Areas\n- Cryptocurrency regulations\n- Digital transaction monitoring\n- Enhanced technological surveillance\n\nThis framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
